To get distro

cat /etc/*-release | grep NAME | head -n1 | cut -d '=' -f2

use popen() to run cmds and return the output 
https://www.baeldung.com/linux/c-code-execute-system-command

makefile
https://linuxhandbook.com/using-make/#initial-draft-of-a-makefile

What needs to be fetched?

os:
    distro, kernel

cpu:
    brand/model, cpu frequency, cpu core and thread count

memory: 
    max, in-use, percentage, free

gpu: 
    brand/model 


For benchmarking :3

time kittfetch >/dev/null

bool_options & 2^n, for storing all bool options in a single uint32
